Almost half of those with severe allergies live in daily fear of suffering a potentially fatal reaction . 
  Yet many Britons are unaware of the seriousness of the condition . 
  Poll of 2,000 adults to mark Allergy Awareness Week reveals two thirds would not know how to help if they saw someone suffering an allergic reaction . 
  Hospital admissions for allergies increased by 8 per cent between 2013 and 2014 . 
  Around 21million Britons have some kind of allergy . 
 